<div id="intro">A fast and easy way to learn coding skills.</div><div id="tryit"><a href="#" id="button">Start</a></div><div id="indented"><p>Have you ever wondered if you might be good at programming? Here&#39;s the quickest place to find out!</p><p>Here you will gain coding skills using <span style="color:#660000"><strong>E</strong></span><span style="color:#000066"><strong>asy</strong></span><span style="color:#660000"><strong>C</strong></span><span style="color:#000066"><strong>oder</strong></span>, an intuitive, English-like scripting system that avoids the need to learn a complicated programming language. In these tutorial pages you will write scripts that run in any browser, and the skills you develop will leave you well prepared if you decide later to step further into the world of programming, particularly for web based projects.</p><p>Write scripts and immediately run them, using our easy-to-use online script editor (PC version shown below but the system also runs in a smartphone browser). Full guidance is provided in a series of gentle steps with well-documented example code.</p></div><p><img alt="" id="editor" src="resources/img/editor.png" style="width:100%" /></p><p>You can install the <span style="color:#660000"><strong>E</strong></span><span style="color:#000066"><strong>asy</strong></span><span style="color:#660000"><strong>C</strong></span><span style="color:#000066"><strong>oder</strong></span> tutorials on your own computer and run them without needing an internet connection. See <a href="install.html">Installation</a>.</p>